Live coloration. Yellow-orange base (
Fig. 1
), with several ocelli, bluish-white spots ringed with maroon. About 40 or more ocelli on the dorsal surface of carapace and fewer on the external surfaces of the chelipeds. Ambulatory legs with 2–4 ocelli each on the dorsal surfaces of meri, carpi and propodi and white bands at the joints. Third maxillipeds, thoracic sternum and abdomen much lighter in color than the dorsal surfaces, but also decorated with ocelli. Eyes with one ocellus on each eyestalk.
